thread.title: Police Identify Man Who Killed Himself Near White House

author: wsjcom
title: Police Identify Man Who Killed Himself Near White House
text:
0 COMMENTS WASHINGTON—The man who fatally shot himself in front of the White House was a 26-year-old resident of Maylene, Ala., authorities said.
Cameron Ross Burgess approached the fence along the north side of the White House and fired several rounds from a handgun shortly before midday Saturday, police said.
President Donald Trump and first lady Melania Trump were in Florida at the time, and the Secret Service says no member of the president’s family was at the White House then.
None of the shots appeared to have been directed toward the White House, authorities said.
